Basic React App instructions:

- to create a new app: npm create vite@latest
  - enter the project name
  - specify "react" when prompted
  - specify "JavaScript" when prompted
- cd into the project directory
- to install dependencies: npm install
- to open the project in VS Code: code .
- once in VS Code, open a terminal window
- in the terminal window, to start the server in a browser tab run: npm run dev
- changes to the code will automatically be reflected in the browser tab
- debugging can be done using the browser's developer tools (F12)
- to stop the server, in the terminal window press: Ctrl + C
